    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nThe document on option `mousescroll` did not mention that you need to `set nowrap` for it to work. Only in `:h scroll-mouse-wheel`, there is a mention of `nowrap`, but `mousescroll` option is not mentioned there. I do not think any normal user can piece this two info together to figure out how to make `mousescroll` work.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. `nvim --clean some-file.txt`\r\n2. try to scroll left and right with your mouse, nothing happens\r\n3. run `:set nowrap`\r\n4. scroll left and right again with your mouse, now horizontal scroll works\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe doc `mousescroll` can be improved to include the `nowrap` setup.\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.9.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nNA\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 13.3.1\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nwezterm latest release\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nhomebrew",
